cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with improving the performance of collaborative filtering-based recommender systems by incorporating side information in the form of natural language reviews. It also involves the use of neural network models, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also explores different models of reviews, which involves Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) techniques. Finally, the paper uses a dataset from Amazon, which involves Computer Vision (cs.CV) techniques for processing images of products.
